config.general.adminConsoleUrl.desc: Admin console used to manage this server.
config.data-store-module-config.threadDu: Folder to be used to store application thread dumps. This folder must be accessible by application and server.
config.data-store-module-config.recordin: Folder to be used to store application recordings. This folder must be accessible by application and server.
config.data-store-module-config.transfer: Folder to be used to store application uploads and downloads. This folder must be accessible by application and server.
config.general.name: Name
config.general.enabled.desc: If true, application will be started automatically, when server starts.
config.general.icon.desc: Path to icon displayed in application selection dialog. Recommended size 256x256.
config.general.webHomeDir.desc: Application's home directory for web-related content. This will be the base directory of any relative classpath entries specified.
config.general.webFolder.desc: Folder to be used to store customized static web files like HTML, CSS or Javascript.
config.general.restrictedResources.desc: Defined Path-prefix restricts access to resources only to authenticated users. Applies to static resources inside 'Web Folder' or packaged with Webswing.
config.general.langFolder.desc: Folder to be used to store customized messages and translations in supported languages. English is available by default.
config.general.allowedCorsOrigins.desc: If you are embedding webswing to page on different domain, you have to enable Cross-origin resource sharing (CORS) by adding the domain in this list. Use * to allow all domains.
config.security.classPath.desc: Additional classpath for built-in Security module or for defining custom security module.
config.security.module.desc: Select one of built-in modules or enter full class name of custom security module (has to implement org.webswing.server.services.security.api.WebswingSecurityModule interface). Note the class and its dependencies has to be on classpath defined above.
config.security.securityContextPerTab.de: Separate security context for each browser tab.
config.session.sessionMode.desc: Select session behavior when user reconnects to application. 1.ALWAYS_NEW_SESSION: New application is started for every Webswing session. (Session timeout will be set to 0) 2.CONTINUE_FOR_TAB: Webswing session can be resumed within the same browser tab after connection is terminated or user refresh the page. (Session timeout applies)  3.CONTINUE_FOR_BROWSER: Webswing session can be resumed in the same browser after connection is terminated (Session timeout applies). 4.CONTINUE_FOR_USER: Application session can be resumed by the same user from any computer after the connection is terminated(Session timeout applies).
config.session.maxClients.desc: Maximum number of allowed simultaneous connections for this application.
config.session.allowStealSession.desc: If enabled, and session mode 'CONTINUE_FOR_USER' is selected, user can resume Webswing session even if the connection is open in other browser. Former browser window will be disconnected.
config.session.autoLogout.desc: If enabled, user is automatically logged out after the application finished.
config.features.monitorEdtEnabled.desc: If True, Webswing will display a progress animation if Swing's Event Dispatch thread is not responding.
config.features.loadingAnimationDelay.de: If EDT thread is blocked for more then defined delay in seconds, dialog with loading animation is displayed appears. Delay must be  >= 2 seconds.
config.features.recordingConsentRequired: If enabled, triggering Session recording from admin console will show a dialog for users to provide their consent before Session recording is started
config.features.mirroringConsentRequired: If enabled, triggering Mirror View from admin console will show a dialog for users to provide their consent before Mirror View is started
config.features.uploadMaxSize.desc: Maximum size of upload for single file (in MB). Set 0 for unlimited size.
config.data-store.classPath.desc: Additional classpath for built-in data store module or for defining custom data store module.
config.data-store.module.desc: Select one of built-in modules or enter full class name of custom data store module (has to implement org.webswing.server.common.datastore.WebswingDataStoreModule interface). Note the class and its dependencies has to be on classpath defined above.
config.general.homeDir.desc: Application's home directory. This will be the base directory of any relative classpath entries specified.
config.general.theme.desc: Select one of the default window decoration themes or a enter path to a XFWM4 theme folder.
config.general.fontConfig.desc: Customize logical font mappings and define physical fonts available to application. These fonts (TTF only) will be used for DirectDraw as native fonts. Key: name of font (ie. dialog|dialoginput|sansserif|serif|monospaced), Value: path to font file.
config.general.directdraw.desc: DirectDraw rendering mode uses canvas instructions to render the application instead of server-rendered png images. DirectDraw improves performance but is not recomended for applications with lot of graphics content.
config.general.javaFx.desc: Enables native or embeded JavaFx framework support.
config.general.javaFxClassPathEntries.de: (Only valid for Java 11+) JavaFX jar libraries to be included in classpath. Supports ? and * wildcards.
config.general.debug.desc: Enables remote debug for this application. To start the application in debug mode use '?debugPort=8000' url param.
config.general.testMode.desc: Enables test mode for this application to be able to test it in Webswing Test Tool.
config.java.userDir.desc: The User working directory. Path from which the application process will be started. (See the Java System Property: 'user.dir')
config.java.jreExecutable.desc: Path to java executable that will be used to spawn application process. Java 8 and 11 are supported.
config.java.javaVersion.desc: Java version of the JRE executable defined above. Expected values are starting with '1.8' or '11'.
config.java.classPathEntries.desc: Application's classpath. Absolute or relative path to jar file or classes directory. At least one classPath entry should be specified containing the main class. Supports ? and * wildcards.
config.java.vmArgs.desc: Commandline arguments processed by Oracle's Java Virtual Machine. (ie. '-Xmx128m')
config.java.launcherType.desc: Select the application type. Applet or regular Desktop Application.
config.launcher-configuration.appletClas: Applet's fully qualiffied main class name. Must implement the java.applet.Applet interface. (ie. 'com.mypackage.MyApplet')
config.launcher-configuration.parameters: Applets start parameters. Set of key-value pairs accessible to applet at startup.
config.session.swingSessionTimeout.desc: Specifies how long (seconds) will be the application left running after the user closes the browser. User can reconnect in this interval and continue in last session.
config.session.timeoutIfInactive.desc: If True, the Session Timeout will apply for user inactivity (Session Timeout has to be > 0). Otherwise only disconnected sessions will time out.
config.logging.sessionLogging.desc: If enabled, sessions are logged into a separate log file.
config.logging.allowStatisticsLogging.de: If enabled, statistics will be logged for sessions.
config.logging.sessionLogFileSize.desc: Maximum size of all session log files. After file size is exceeded, old log files are deleted.
config.features.isolatedFs.desc: If true, every file chooser dialog will be restricted to access only the home directory of current application.
config.features.allowUpload.desc: If selected, the JFileChooser integration will allow users to upload files to folder opened in the file chooser dialog
config.features.allowDelete.desc: If selected, the JFileChooser integration will allow users to delete files displayed in the file chooser dialog
config.features.allowDownload.desc: If selected, the JFileChooser integration will allow users to download files displayed in the file chooser dialog
config.features.transparentFileOpen.desc: If selected, the JFileChooser dialog's open mode will open a client side file browser and transparently upload selected files and triggers selection.
config.features.transparentFileSave.desc: If selected, the JFileChooser dialog's save mode will open a client side dialog to enter the file name to be saved.
config.features.transferDir.desc: If Isolated Filesystem is enabled. This will be the folder on the server where the user can upload and download files from. Multiple folders can be defined using path separator (${path.separator})
config.features.clearTransferDir.desc: If enabled, all files in the transfer folder will be deleted when the application process is terminated.
config.features.allowJsLink.desc: If enabled, the JSLink feature will be enabled, allowing application to invoke javascript and vice versa. (See netscape.javascript.JSObject)
config.features.jsLinkWhitelist.desc: List of allowed Java classes. Calls to declared methods of these classes are allowed via JsLink. Supports trailing * wildcard. Use single * entry to allow any class. Leave empty to disallow everything. E.g. org.webswing.*
config.features.allowLocalClipboard.desc: Enables built-in integration of client's local clipboard. Due to browser security limitations clipboard toolbar is displayed.
config.features.allowServerPrinting.desc: Enables native printing on devices configured on server's OS. If disabled a pdf is generated and sent to client browser.
config.features.dockMode.desc: Select the mode for undocking windows to a separate browser window: 1.ALL: all windows can be undocked. 2.MARKED: only windows marked with Dockable interface can be undocked. 3.NONE: disable undocking
config.features.allowAutoDownload.desc: If selected, the JFileChooser dialog's save mode will trigger file download as soon as the selected file is available on filesystem.
Swing application fully qualiffied class name. (ie. 'com.mypackage.Main')
config.launcher-configuration.args.desc: Swing application main method arguments. This string will be passed to the main method's (String[] args)
config.data-store.directTransfer.desc: If enabled, file transfer between browser and application will use WebSocket connection. Use this option if your deployment doesn't allow shared access to single data store.
config.security-module-config-general.lo: Webswing will redirect to this URL after logout. If empty, user is redirected to login page.
